Jim Mostek wrote:
> Has the issue of a file_operation callout for fcntl gone around before?
> Anyone opposed to adding this? I don't think this belongs in the
> inode_operations.
If you do it, remember that all the extra F_* codes must be listed in
<asm/fcntl.h> or <linux/fcntl.h> -- not an fs-specific header, because
they mustn't conflict with the normal F_* codes.  Ever.
enjoy,
-- Jamie
